        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 9:09PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 909 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles west of Campo, or 22 miles south of Springfield, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Campo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Locally heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may
lead to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through
flooded roadways.</instruction>
